videos.description: Quarterback Skylar Thompson keeps the ball and runs 5 yards to cap off a drive during which he ran for a total of 65 yards.
videos.headline: Kansas State strikes first with short TD run

videos.description: Mason Rudolph drops back and finds James Washington downfield for a 38-yard score to tie the game in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Rudolph throws 38-yard TD pass for Cowboys

videos.description: Skylar Thompson throws a 47-yard pass to Byron Pringle, who finds the end zone for a Kansas State touchdown.
videos.headline: Thompson throws perfect TD pass to Pringle

videos.description: Byron Pringle receives the kick, slips a tackle and returns it 89 yards to the house to extend Kansas State's lead.
videos.headline: Pringle returns kick 89 yards for Wildcat TD

videos.description: Mason Rudolph goes deep and his pass is picked off by Duke Shelly to give the Wildcats the ball on their own 18-yard line.
videos.headline: Rudolph picked off by Kansas State defense

videos.description: Mason Rudolph's pass is intercepted by Kendall Adams who returns it 20 yards to give the Wildcats the ball back in their own territory.
videos.headline: Rudolph throws second pick of the game

videos.description: Alex Barnes finds a hole and breaks for a 39-yard touchdown run to extend the Wildcats' lead before halftime.
videos.headline: Kansas State extends lead with nice TD run

videos.description: Oklahoma State head coach Mike Gundy says that his quarterback needs to settle down in the second half, but that starts with being in a better position on defense.
videos.headline: Gundy wants improvement on all sides of the ball in the second half

videos.description: Skylar Thompson finds Byron Pringle for a 46-yard touchdown to add to Kansas State's lead.
videos.headline: Pringle strikes again with 46-yard TD catch

videos.description: Skylar Thompson throws a deep pass to Byron Pringle for the 60-yard score marking his fourth total touchdown of the day.
videos.headline: Pringle continues to dominate with 3rd receiving TD

videos.description: Justice Hill runs to the outside and dives for the pylon to cut Kansas State's lead in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State answers with short TD run

videos.description: James Washington hauls in a deep pass from Mason Rudolph to put Oklahoma State in scoring position.
videos.headline: Rudolph finds Washington for 52-yard gain

videos.description: Mason Rudolph keeps it and runs into the end zone from the 2-yard line to make it a two-possession game.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State comes back with Rudolph TD

videos.description: Skylar Thompson fumbles the ball as he is sacked and the Cowboys recover it to give them the ball in Kansas State territory.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State gets timely turnover

videos.description: Mason Rudolph connects with Dillon Stoner for a 14-yard score, but the Cowboys fail to get the two-point conversion.
videos.headline: Rudolph TD makes it a one-possession game

videos.description: Ahmad Brooks and Anish Shroff break down Skylar Thompson and Byron Pringle's big performance in K-State's 45-40 win over Oklahoma State.
videos.headline: Thompson and Pringle key in Kansas State's big road win
